QOOBAR v.1.7.0 INSTALLATION:
---------------------------

** Linux
--------

Manual compilation:

For debian-based systems:
Make sure you have libqt4-dev (>=4.6) or qtbase5-dev installed.
Also install libdiscid0, libflac8, flac, shntool, enca.

For rpm-based systems:
Make sure you have libqt4-devel >= 4.6 installed.
Also install libdiscid1, libflac8, flac.

In the console type:
$ qmake
$ make
$ sudo make install
$ make clean

Or you can install qoobar from deb or rpm package
  (see http://qoobar.sourceforge.net/en/download.htm).


** Windows
----------

Manual compilation: (MinGW support only)

1. Install Qt/Windows Open Source Edition >= 4.5.0
2. Download http://sourceforge.net/projects/qoobar/files/utils/win_utils.tar.gz
   archive with necessary dlls and execs and unpack it into qoobar-1.7.0
3. Build manually:

> qmake
> mingw32-make
> mingw32-make clean

4. Copy release/* files to desired location or run release/qoobar.exe

Or you can install qoobar from
http://sourceforge.net/projects/qoobar/files/qoobar-1.7.0/Windows/qoobar-1.7.0.exe/download

** Mac OS X
-----------

Manual compilation:

1. Install Qt SDK
2. Download http://sourceforge.net/projects/qoobar/files/utils/mac_os_utils.tar.gz
   archive with necessary libs and execs and unpack it into qoobar-1.7.0
3. qmake && make && make install

Or you can install qoobar from
http://sourceforge.net/projects/qoobar/files/qoobar-1.7.0/Mac_OS_X/qoobar-1.7.0.dmg/download
